item.title: Client Problem... :s Still no answer ffs
item.dc:creator: @Random666 Random666
item.description:
@Random666 wrote:

Happend to me once but i fixed it. what you do is…
1)Go to “My Computer”
2)On the left side, there’s a link saying “view system information”. Click that
3)Go to the advanced tab, and on the bottom you’ll see a tab saying “system variables”. Click that.
4)Under User variables, if you see two variables, one “CLASSPATH” and one “PATH”. Deleted them.

If You dont’t have those variables, I dont know what to do soz. Maybe add them instead?
